● What kinds of issues might you run into with your API? This is especially important
if you are creating your own API, web scraping produces notoriously messy data.
- My data was not being sent to mongoDB it was deploying correctly and the data was not being
sent correctly. I had to run a few tests before actually getting it to work. 

● Is there any sensitive information you need to secure?
- I would say yes, the app secures the password of the user and their personal information. 

Like, email, age, password and once they log in their information is stored in a secured
database. 
● What functionality will your app include?
- It includes a login, registration, logout, profile, and track component that would 
help users navigate to different options in the app.

● What will the user flow look like?
- First, they need to sign up with email, password, and age. After they are logged in, they
would be able to login with their email and password. The age is necessary to know the age of the 
user and if they are younger than 12, then it won't let them to sign in.

● What features make your site more than a CRUD app? What are your stretch
goals?
- My stretch goal in this application is for the users necessities to be met. I want the
users to be able to use this application throughout their day and make it easy for them
 to navigate and store their information. Also, avoiding interrumptions as much as possble,
like crashing or slowing down. This application should be easy and simple to use.

